In The Bottom Of A Hole<br>
Where Peace Will Never Fit In.<br>
   I feel so strange to be laying my words on this screen. Doing so tells me that I don't believe myself when I say: I at last carry my crosses with resignation. The screaming in my heart is a fixture in my vitals that I will not outlive in this life.  I will try once again to breath clean air by telling my silly tale of real rage and immagined wrongs.   Of situations where there are no right actions, only evils to choose among to survive the day, then the night, then the day...   Maby I won't, there's no help to be had by it, and who could possabily give a shit.  <br>
   I keep reading about this cognitave whatever-it-is where heart and head are on different headings tword an IP in a personal one each type two without bipod hell.   That folks is my I'm-sorry-for-me pass at humor.   Nam cost me a leg as well as a soul.   No, that's not right, without the soul this pain would only be in the body.   I am so very tired... too tired...  it's late.  I get these dreams, and I hate it.  How I do whine on.<br>
I think I need to stop.   I'm rambling.<br>
   No one here anyhow...   me a talking to me...<br>
good night me.
